# Mobile App Specification

Before building mobile features or `/api/mobile/v1/*` BFF routes, read **`docs/MOBILE_APP_SPEC.md`**.

## Key constraints

- **Admin-only** mobile app; students denied at login
- **Android first**, then iOS personal use only (Expo SDK 52+, Expo Router, Clerk Expo, TanStack Query)
- **Zero EAS cost** — local builds (`expo prebuild`, `expo run:*`); optional GitHub Actions free tier for Android AABs; manual Play Console upload. **Do not use paid EAS Build/Submit/Update.**
- **Distribution:** Google Play production (Console already owned); iOS solo device via Xcode sideload or optional TestFlight ($99/yr Apple Developer) — no public App Store listing
- **No Supabase keys in mobile** — all data via server BFF with Bearer JWT + `requireAdmin()`
- **Phase 0 backend blockers:** Bearer auth in `requireAuth()`, mobile BFF routes, admin guard hardening, `GET /api/mobile/v1/me`

## Domain

Production: `https://www.mentorbridge.in`

## When editing

- New mobile endpoints → follow schemas in spec §8–9
- Reuse existing APIs where noted (assignments, session-videos, cohorts, gallery, etc.)
- Do not expose `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` secrets to mobile clients
